---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="About" description="What Cornfed Bucks is and who it's for.">
  <section class="about">
    <div class="wrap about__inner">
      <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
      <h1>Hunting between the rows.</h1>
      <p>
        Most whitetail content is written for big timber — mountain benches, river-bottom hardwoods,
        thousand-acre public tracts. That's not the hunting most of us in corn and bean country actually do.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cornfed Bucks is for hunters working real Midwest ag ground: a leased 80, a family farm,
        a fence line between two fields that's the only cover for half a mile. The strategy here
        starts from that reality — edges instead of interiors, combine schedules instead of just
        moon phases, and small sanctuary acres instead of big food plot budgets.
      </p>
      <p>
        New field notes go up through the season, and the Monday Morning Report newsletter covers
        what changed in the woods — and in the fields — over the past week.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .about { padding: 3.5rem 0 5rem; }
  .about__inner { max-width: 620px; }
  .about h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4vw, 2.6rem);
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
  }
  .about p {
    margin: 0 0 1.2rem;
    font-size: 1.02rem;
  }
</style>
